Commentary: floated down full, on off stump, and it's driven to long off for a single
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: Fakhar comes down the track, but he's not nearly to the pitch and is saved by a big bottom edge, the ball bouncing hard into the turf and allowing him an extra moment to scurry back to the crease
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: Fakhar skips out again, and this time slaps his shot out to deep midwicket
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run
Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, no run

Commentary: Fakhar backs right away to leg and sets himself before Ilyas has even delivered, but the bowler follows him and he wears one on the thigh pad
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, 1 leg bye
Mohammad Ilyas to Salman Butt, 1 run
Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: just past the off stump! Ilyas possibly just surprised Fakhar with this one, which slipped out as a full toss but dipped as it got to him, beating his swipe and almost crashing into the stumps
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: on a length, and it's cracked to point. Fakhar wants a single, but there's none to be had
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: flat-batted down the ground! It ain't pretty, but it's mighty effective. Fakhar clears his left leg and hacks at a length delivery, getting a good connection to send the ball back over young Ilyas' head, and that's also the team fifty up at the end of the Powerplay
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: looped down on middle and off, Butt looks to manufacture something but he can't get it away
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, no run

Commentary: Butt hops out to drive, but sends the ball straight at the cover fielder
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, no run

Commentary: and he lets his bottom hand do the work this time, slapping the ball down to long on
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: too short from Malik, Fakhar cutting in front of square and pressing hard for the second run
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, 2 runs

Commentary: this one rushes on with the arm, Fakhar waiting deep in his crease and forcing off the back foot for a single
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: flicked off the pad, through square leg, for a single
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: pushed through too far outside the off stump
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Salman Butt, 1 wide

Commentary: slapped to cover, a quick single the result
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: down the ground! Fakhar is into the 30s now, giving himself room but keeping his head still. Excellent connection on the stroke, and it goes all the way
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: Ilyas hits a length outside off, and the ball races down to third man off a thick edge
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: full, straight, and Butt turns the strike back over with a single to square leg
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: not a hint of a slog about this one, Fakhar stepping right across to the off side and picking a length ball up back over his own head with a Dilscoop. Timed it well, and it went all the way
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: and this one scorches through cover! Ilyas wanted this to be a yorker, but it slipped out as a full toss, and worse still, it was outside off stump. Fakhar laces his shot through the covers, and that's 20 from the over
Commentary_short: Mohammad Ilyas to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: Butt skips down the track, but he's not to the pitch. Still, he manages to find space in the covers to turn the strike back over
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: tapped to point, another quick single the result
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: Butt is down the track again, and this time he chips his drive. But it's not a great connection, and the ball is pulled in before the boundary line
Commentary_short: Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 2 runs
Shoaib Malik to Salman Butt, 1 run
Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs
Shoaib Malik to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: speared in flat and fast, and it's tapped to long on for a single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: too short, but Irfan gets away with it as there's cover in the deep to stop the pull shot
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: slapped hard down to long off, one more
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Fakhar Zaman, 1 run

Commentary: Butt cuts, but he finds the point fielder with his shot and there's no room for a single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Salman Butt, no run

Commentary: short, wide and it's swatted in the air over cover, the ball falling short of a the sweeper fielder out there
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: the top edge sails all the way! Fakhar's clearly got a good eye, he must have quite some bat too. He bent into a slog sweep but looked to have top edged this one, only for the ball to keep going and going all the way over the boundary
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Fakhar Zaman, SIX runs

Commentary: Butt turns the strike back over once again, with a single off his pads
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Salman Butt, 1 run

Commentary: back of a length and very nippy from Junaid, the ball zipping past Fakhar's swat into the leg side and striking him on the body
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Fakhar Zaman, no run

Commentary: another scoop and this one also comes off handsomely! The ball was on a length and straight, and he picked the length up early - as well as noting that the fielder was up at short fine leg. He got it up and over him, and that also brings up the team 100
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Fakhar Zaman, FOUR runs

Commentary: Junaid Khan strikes in his first over and it's a huge blow! Fakhar took on the fielder at deep midwicket, but he didn't get as much of a connection as he would have liked and Evans held a simple catch in that position. This will dent the chase just a little ...
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Fakhar Zaman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Fakhar Zaman c Evans b Junaid Khan 63 (35b 7x4 3x6) SR: 180.00

Commentary: AB is off the mark straight away, angling the ball through gully for one
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: bowled him! Double strike. Salman Butt needed to get a move on, and he backed away to the leg side, looking to open up the covers. But Junaid was unfazed, firing in a quick delivery full and straight to rattle the stumps
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Salman Butt, OUT
Dismissal_text: Salman Butt  b Junaid Khan 17 (19b 1x4 0x6) SR: 89.47

Commentary: de Villiers hops in the air to ride the extra bounce, and finds the gap at gully for a single
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Irfan hits a splice-jarring length outside off, and there's a big swish and a miss from Agha Salman
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: rising off a length once again, and Salman can't get this one away either
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: Salman forces off the back foot, and such is the bounce that he can't keep the shot down, but places it past point. Cover sweeper cleans up
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, 2 runs

Commentary: oof! Irfan bends his back and the ball leaps alarmingly up at Salman, who does well just to keep it off his face
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: and now he backs away, but this bounce is just too much for him as another delivery leaps off a short length and past his flailing cut shot
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Agha Salman, no run

Commentary: around the wicket comes Junaid, targeting the stumps, and AB can only tap it back to him
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, no run

Commentary: AB shuffles in the crease, opening up his stance and finding the gap at cover with a backfoot push
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Junaid strikes again! Short, quick and Agha Salman had no answer, top edging his attempted pull. Umar Siddiq, keeping wicket, does the rest, holding a simple chance. These quick strikes are really hurting Qalandars
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Agha Salman, OUT
Dismissal_text: Agha Salman c †Umar Siddiq b Junaid Khan 2 (6b 0x4 0x6) SR: 33.33

Commentary: AB waits in the crease and flicks his wrists over a length ball, picking the gap at midwicket
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Taylor's off the mark straight away, but he's in some serious trouble too. He tapped the ball into the leg side, but as soon as he set off something went in his calf, and he completed the single in apparently severe discomfort. He's helped to the ground by the opposition players at the other end, clutching his calf, and the physio runs out to attend to him. This is not good. He has to be helped, limping, from the field. He may have torn a calf muscle, and he's unable to continue
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Taylor, 1 run

Commentary: there's a beautiful crunch off the bat as de Villiers places a length delivery through point, and they press hard for a third run ... but what's this, AB drops his bat pushing for the third run, and he has to sprint extra hard to get his foot in in time. Fortunately for his team, he does so
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 3 runs

Commentary: Irfan aims full, de Villiers drives a single to mid off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese is off the mark straight away with a quick single, dropping a short ball close in on the off side and setting off
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: short, and rising over leg stump, de Villiers gloving his pull into the leg side
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese collects a single down to third man with an angled bat
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: up and over mid off! De Villiers swatted a short ball up and over the off side field, and without a man out on the boundary it was four all the way
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to de Villiers, FOUR runs

Commentary: and a quick single off the final delivery allows de Villiers to keep the strike
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: punched down to long on, just the one
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: chipped in the air through midwicket, and they sprint through for the second
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, 2 runs

Commentary: full and straight, and Wiese's drive is mistimed to cover
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, no run

Commentary: straight down the ground! Wiese spotted another full length delivery and he had a go at this one. For a moment it looked like he might have got more height than distance in the shot, but he's got enough on it to clear the rope
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, SIX runs

Commentary: Junaid's response is a short ball, Wiese collecting a single with a short-arm jab to midwicket
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: de Villiers keeps the strike with a drive down the ground
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: a touch short, and spinning away from the right hander, but de Villiers' shot is stopped by the cover sweeper
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese punches into the covers, and a slightly wild shy at the non-striker's end allows them back for a second - and keeps Wiese on strike
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Wiese, 2 runs

Commentary: a couple of steps down the track, and a huge mow down the ground! Wiese got right to the pitch of it and sliced an aerial drive right out of the middle
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Wiese, SIX runs

Commentary: so he gives this one much less air, Wiese waiting in the crease and cutting through point
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: googly from Irfan, and de Villiers picks it, pulling in the air to midwicket ... but he doesn't get all of it, and it's just the one
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: another one! This is up onto the roof. Monstrous strike. Again Wiese dances out to meet the ball, and again he makes a mighty connection
Commentary_short: Mohammad Irfan(4) to Wiese, SIX runs

Commentary: Russell ambles in and delivers a full ball at 129km/h, de Villiers walks across and flicks an incredible scoop up and over short fine leg
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, FOUR runs

Commentary: he makes some room, backing away to leg, but Russell aims full and wide and he can only just lay bat to ball
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: full, and a Wiese drive turns the strike back over
Commentary_short: Russell to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: powered down the ground! De Villiers seizes on a floaty, full ball, spanking it straight back down the ground, and all along the turf. The shot also raises the fifty stand between these two
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, FOUR runs

Commentary: Russell aims full and wide again, de Villiers threading his drive through point
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese is perhaps taken a little by surprise as Russell slips in a short one, but he manages to put bat to ball and find a single to midwicket - keeping the strike
Commentary_short: Russell to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: Wiese charges the bowler, but he can't do much with a yorker outside off, jabbing it through point
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: AB misses out! Junaid bustles in and delivers a wide full toss outside off. De Villiers doesn't manage to put bat to ball, and it's not called wide - though it was marginal
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, no run

Commentary: sliced over extra cover! As soon as it's there to be hit, AB does so. Junaid only misses his length by a couple of inches, but de Villiers punished him for it, bending very low to get under the ball and hammer it over extra cover
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, SIX runs

Commentary: that's better from Junaid, right up to the bat and AB can't get underneath it
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: a wicket off a no-ball! Wiese was aiming for the stands but sliced right underneath the ball, Malik running across from the covers to hold an excellent high catch under pressure. But it doesn't matter, because Junaid's heel isn't behind the line as he delivers. To make matters worse, here comes a Free Hit - and de Villiers is on strike
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to Wiese, 1 no ball

Commentary: how do words do justice to this shot? Only de Villiers can play them like this. He sets himself early for a reverse-scoop, and the ball is just the one he wants: a full toss. De Villiers turns his stance around and lifts it over third man, and the entire stadium is chanting his name
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, SIX runs

Commentary: Junaid pulls his length back, but de Villiers can only find a single off his pull. However, he does keep the strike
Commentary_short: Junaid Khan to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: up, up, up into the night sky and out of the ground! Russell offers a gentle length delivery, and de Villiers sends the ball back even faster than it arrived. A 91-metre hit
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, SIX runs

Commentary: a scooped drive balloons up and over point, but it evades the back-peddling fielder. Just the single
Commentary_short: Russell to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: over fine leg! Wiese can hit them too. Russell chanced a short ball, but Wiese got back and across and muscled it all the way over the boundary
Commentary_short: Russell to Wiese, SIX runs
Russell to Wiese, 1 run
Russell to de Villiers, 1 run

Commentary: Russell goes for the yorker, it's a low full toss and the ball is clipped out to deep midwicket. Wiese keeps the strike
Commentary_short: Russell to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: in the air, but safe! Wiese mistimes his swipe into the leg side, but hits it so badly it doesn't reach the boundary fielder
Commentary_short: Christian to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: yorker from Christian, a slower one, and de Villiers can't get it away but they take a run off his boot
Commentary_short: Christian to de Villiers, 1 leg bye

Commentary: slashed in the air, but again the ball lands short of the fielder, this time at long off
Commentary_short: Christian to Wiese, 1 run

Commentary: a full toss, and it's a rare mis-hit from de Villiers, who tries to slog sweep it away. The ball bounces in front of the midwicket fielder, and they sprint back for a second
Commentary_short: Christian to de Villiers, 2 runs

Commentary: through his legs! Cracking delivery. Christian delivers another pinpoint yorker, and AB can't get bat on it but they pinch a single as it flicks the pad on the way to the keeper
Commentary_short: Christian to de Villiers, 1 leg bye

Commentary: forget about it! They needed three, and Wiese gives them six. The players charge out onto the field. The ball was full, but not full enough. Wiese got underneath it, and powered it all the way over the rope
Commentary_short: Christian to Wiese, SIX runs
